        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:51PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 151 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wellington, or 14 miles north of Fort Collins, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wellington, Nunn, Carr and Rockport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
